    "pathophysiology": "EBV infects B-lymphocytes via CD21 receptor. Polyclonal B-cell activation triggers vigorous cytotoxic CD8+ T-cell response producing characteristic atypical lymphocytes (Downey cells). Hepatic involvement: EBV infects hepatocytes and biliary epithelium; immune-mediated injury causes mild self-limited hepatitis with ALT elevation typically 2-5x ULN. Hepatitis results from both direct viral infection and T-cell mediated inflammation targeting infected cells in the liver.",
